Step 1: Identify the net profit.  
• From the income statement, the net profit is 707199.17.

Step 2: Calculate the average total assets.  
• The balance sheet shows the total assets at the beginning (2023-12-31) as 13000000.00 and at the end (2024-01-29) as 15200446.16.  
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
  = (13000000.00 + 15200446.16) / 2  
  = 28200446.16 / 2  
  = 14100223.08

Step 3: Calculate Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (707199.17 / 14100223.08) × 100%  
  ≈ 0.05017 × 100%  
  ≈ 5.02%

Thus, the ROA is approximately 5.02%.
